What are you trying to say?

57:09.702 --> 57:13.153
That I have five more
years to have a baby?

57:13.188 --> 57:16.674
That my clock is ticking?

57:16.709 --> 57:18.883
That my fertility
begins to decline

57:18.918 --> 57:20.644
as soon as I'm 30 years old?

57:23.612 --> 57:26.201
That probabilities
of having a baby

57:26.235 --> 57:30.447
with a chromosomal abnormality
after 30 is one in 385?

57:32.897 --> 57:34.589
Is that what you're
trying to say?

57:36.487 --> 57:39.490
Seriously, sometimes
I cannot stand

57:39.525 --> 57:41.596
the comments that you make.

57:41.630 --> 57:44.150
[light music]

57:49.914 --> 57:52.745
[phone vibrating]

57:56.576 --> 57:57.646
[Giancarlo] Hey.

57:57.681 --> 58:00.477
[Rocio on phone] Hey,
what are you doing?

58:01.408 --> 58:02.237
Working.

58:03.549 --> 58:05.412
I need a big favor.

58:05.447 --> 58:06.862
Yeah?

58:06.897 --> 58:10.141
Can you go to the bank and
transfer some money to my mom?

58:10.176 --> 58:11.729
Right now?

58:11.764 --> 58:12.592
Yes.

58:14.214 --> 58:16.251
I can't. I'm working.

58:16.285 --> 58:17.804
Working on the DMV app,

58:17.839 --> 58:19.530
and the deadline is
tomorrow morning.

58:19.565 --> 58:20.807
I thought you said
you were gonna work

58:20.842 --> 58:22.188
on that in the morning.

58:22.222 --> 58:25.847
Yeah, but I decided to sleep
a bit more and start later.

58:25.881 --> 58:29.367
Plus, I mean, the bank
would be closed very soon.

58:29.402 --> 58:32.578
Can you go now and keep
working on that later?

58:32.612 --> 58:34.407
It'll take you
less than an hour.

58:34.441 --> 58:37.583
The money, it's to
pay my mom's mortgage.

58:38.963 --> 58:41.241
Honey, I'm sorry but I
can't. I need to finish this.

58:41.276 --> 58:42.864
They're beta testing first
thing tomorrow morning,

58:42.898 --> 58:46.315
and they pay me a lot
of money to deliver.

58:46.350 --> 58:48.939
Honey, why can't you
go? It's your mom.

58:51.251 --> 58:53.495
You know what? It's fine.

58:53.530 --> 58:56.187
I'll figure it out, like always.

58:56.222 --> 58:56.912
-Hello?
-[phone beeps]

58:57.568 --> 58:58.396
Hello?

59:00.088 --> 59:02.090
[speaking foreign language]

59:04.402 --> 59:05.852
[sighing]

59:05.887 --> 59:08.545
[phone dinging]

59:24.215 --> 59:25.838
What happened?

59:25.872 --> 59:28.461
I went to the grocery store.
I need help with the bags.

59:29.635 --> 59:31.291
Were you able to
do the transfer?

59:32.361 --> 59:33.742
Like you care.

59:33.777 --> 59:35.917
I do. I just didn't have time.

59:35.951 --> 59:37.850
You know, the coding is
getting more complicated

59:37.884 --> 59:38.989
than it should be.

59:39.023 --> 59:40.300
I don't wanna discuss it.

59:40.335 --> 59:42.786
I am tired, and I
don't wanna argue.

59:42.820 --> 59:45.133
You know, sometimes I feel,
Rocio, that working from home

59:45.167 --> 59:47.618
from your point of view
is not really working.

59:47.653 --> 59:49.378
For it means that I
have always extra time.

59:49.413 --> 59:50.345
I never said that.

59:50.379 --> 59:51.622
But you act like that.

59:51.657 --> 59:52.968
Just tell me one time
that I ever called you

59:53.003 --> 59:55.315
at your work to do
something for me, just one.

59:56.696 --> 59:58.767
If you would ever
call me to my work

59:58.802 --> 1:00:01.252
to do something for
you, I would do it.

1:00:01.287 --> 1:00:02.978
The problem is that you
never wanna do anything

1:00:03.013 --> 1:00:04.186
that doesn't relate with you.

1:00:04.221 --> 1:00:06.361
Well it's not true,
because I'm always busy.

1:00:06.395 --> 1:00:07.224
Always busy.

1:00:10.227 --> 1:00:13.920
Why would you ask me why mom
called me the last minute, huh?

1:00:14.783 --> 1:00:16.613
Like I know why she did it.

1:00:16.647 --> 1:00:17.993
I don't know, okay.

1:00:18.028 --> 1:00:20.720
All I know is I'm her
daughter. She needed the money.

1:00:20.755 --> 1:00:23.861
And I ask you for help.
You're my boyfriend, okay.

1:00:23.896 --> 1:00:25.138
The person that I live with.

1:00:25.173 --> 1:00:26.484
You're supposed to
be there for me.

1:00:26.519 --> 1:00:28.694
If I ask something from
you, you should do it.

1:00:28.728 --> 1:00:29.660
End of discussion.

1:00:29.695 --> 1:00:31.041
What? Not end of discussion.

1:00:31.075 --> 1:00:31.973
What are you talking about?

1:00:32.007 --> 1:00:33.250
Because if my job is affected,

1:00:33.284 --> 1:00:34.596
who's going to help me
to pay my bills, huh?

1:00:34.631 --> 1:00:36.667
Your mom? Oh, I don't think so.

1:00:36.702 --> 1:00:38.151
I love your mom. You know I do.

1:00:38.186 --> 1:00:39.981
But she needs to leave
her pride at the door

1:00:40.015 --> 1:00:41.741
and ask for help with time.

1:00:41.776 --> 1:00:43.605
Everybody works
in different ways.

1:00:43.640 --> 1:00:44.951
You need to understand that.

1:00:44.986 --> 1:00:46.953
I do understand when
her poor decisions

1:00:46.988 --> 1:00:48.783
are affecting other people.

1:00:48.817 --> 1:00:51.889
[gasps] You prick.

1:00:53.788 --> 1:00:55.306
I'm not saying it like that.

1:00:55.341 --> 1:00:59.000
I'm just, I want her to be
more organized. That's all.

1:00:59.034 --> 1:01:02.659
Who are you to tell her
what to do and how to do it?

1:01:03.970 --> 1:01:06.007
What she does and
how she does it

1:01:06.041 --> 1:01:07.905
is up to her, not to you.

1:01:07.940 --> 1:01:09.148
Oh yeah?

1:01:09.182 --> 1:01:10.632
Don't you think it would
be better if she tell you

1:01:10.667 --> 1:01:12.151
at least one week before
the payment was up?

1:01:12.185 --> 1:01:14.360
Yeah, yeah, it would
have been better.

1:01:14.394 --> 1:01:17.087
But it didn't happen
that way. Deal with it.

1:01:18.295 --> 1:01:20.228
You know, it's nine PM,
you just came from work.

1:01:20.262 --> 1:01:21.850
I'm still working on the app.

1:01:22.851 --> 1:01:24.335
We're very busy people, Rocio.

1:01:24.370 --> 1:01:27.304
I just want her to ask us
with more time, that's all.

1:01:28.615 --> 1:01:29.755
Busy people?

1:01:31.757 --> 1:01:32.965
Let me show you busy.

1:01:34.414 --> 1:01:36.140
What are you doing?

1:01:40.766 --> 1:01:41.559
Let's see.

1:01:42.595 --> 1:01:44.217
Barbecue with friends.

1:01:46.564 --> 1:01:47.911
Natalie's wedding.

1:01:49.706 --> 1:01:51.362
My mom's birthday.

1:01:52.398 --> 1:01:53.710
The river trip.

1:01:55.125 --> 1:01:57.334
Where are you in all
these pictures, Giancarlo?

1:01:59.267 --> 1:02:00.544
Nowhere.

1:02:00.578 --> 1:02:04.065
This is not about
being busy or not.

1:02:04.099 --> 1:02:06.481
This is about you
not wanting anything

1:02:06.515 --> 1:02:09.277
to interfere with your life.

1:02:09.311 --> 1:02:11.417
And anything that
doesn't interest you,

1:02:11.451 --> 1:02:12.867
you just don't care.

1:02:12.901 --> 1:02:14.420
Even if I do.

1:02:15.801 --> 1:02:18.562
You don't live alone
anymore. You live with me.

1:02:18.596 --> 1:02:20.598
And that alone would
alter your little

1:02:20.633 --> 1:02:22.255
bubble of self-indulgence.

1:02:22.290 --> 1:02:23.498
Really?

1:02:23.532 --> 1:02:24.706
I never pushed anything
on you that you didn't

1:02:24.741 --> 1:02:27.226
wanna do or go to, did I, ever?

1:02:27.260 --> 1:02:29.987
But you still do it, don't you?

1:02:30.022 --> 1:02:32.024
With me or without me.

1:02:33.335 --> 1:02:36.235
Do you think I wanted to go
to that stupid LA convention?

1:02:38.202 --> 1:02:40.204
No, of course I didn't.

1:02:40.239 --> 1:02:43.000
But I did it because I love you.

1:02:43.035 --> 1:02:46.486
Because I wanna see that
part of your world with you.

1:02:47.902 --> 1:02:50.490
You don't wanna see anybody
else's world, just yours.

1:02:51.802 --> 1:02:55.841
You know who does that?
A selfish son of a bitch.

1:03:00.535 --> 1:03:02.813
It wasn't a stupid
convention. You know that.

1:03:04.988 --> 1:03:05.851
It was awesome.

1:03:10.062 --> 1:03:10.890
Shit.

1:03:34.741 --> 1:03:35.570
Rocio?

1:03:37.261 --> 1:03:38.745
I need to go to work.

1:03:38.780 --> 1:03:40.782
Today we close a
deal for Howard.

1:03:42.163 --> 1:03:45.752
I am sorry. I wanna
be there for you.

1:03:49.204 --> 1:03:52.829
Listen, Giancarlo, I know
the transition is hard.

1:03:53.933 --> 1:03:56.211
But when two people
live together,

1:03:56.246 --> 1:03:57.626
there's going to be compromises.

1:03:57.661 --> 1:03:58.835
There's no other way.

1:04:00.353 --> 1:04:01.182
You're right.

1:04:03.391 --> 1:04:04.288
I love you.

1:04:06.843 --> 1:04:08.258
I know.

1:04:08.292 --> 1:04:09.638
I love you too.

1:04:12.193 --> 1:04:13.642
Did you finish the app?

1:04:13.677 --> 1:04:15.990
Yeah. Sent it this morning
before going to sleep.

1:04:16.922 --> 1:04:18.095
When was that?

1:04:18.130 --> 1:04:20.995
Four AM. But I'm sure
they'll be pleased.

1:04:22.030 --> 1:04:22.859
Me too.

1:04:25.620 --> 1:04:26.448
You know,

1:04:29.693 --> 1:04:33.662
it's hard for me to get
used to you working at home.

1:04:35.147 --> 1:04:38.909
I feel like you're
wasting time, but,

1:04:40.393 --> 1:04:42.844
but I need to understand
that that's the way you work.

1:04:42.879 --> 1:04:44.018
I need to respect that.

1:04:45.951 --> 1:04:49.023
[piano music]

1:04:49.057 --> 1:04:50.610
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

1:04:50.645 --> 1:04:51.473
What?

1:04:53.406 --> 1:04:55.270
Really? Let's do one more.

1:04:55.305 --> 1:04:56.582
No, because then, if
we need to go back,

1:04:56.616 --> 1:04:58.756
that'll be three hours and.

1:05:00.103 --> 1:05:01.690
We can jump rope at
home. That'd be more fun.

1:05:01.725 --> 1:05:03.140
You get bored too easily.

1:05:03.175 --> 1:05:05.694
I'm not bored. I'm with you.

1:05:05.729 --> 1:05:06.557
Bite me.

1:05:10.630 --> 1:05:13.461
I love working out around
these beautiful houses.

1:05:15.773 --> 1:05:16.602
Yeah.

1:05:17.983 --> 1:05:22.056
Actually, I was
thinking to buy a house.

1:05:24.161 --> 1:05:25.991
You wanna buy a house now?

1:05:26.025 --> 1:05:28.027
Yeah, with you.

1:05:30.754 --> 1:05:32.411
Oh, well.

1:05:33.722 --> 1:05:35.172
I don't know.

1:05:35.207 --> 1:05:38.106
I was thinking to save at
least for one more year.

1:05:38.141 --> 1:05:39.211
I mean, we've been
living together

1:05:39.245 --> 1:05:41.558
for almost a year now.

1:05:41.592 --> 1:05:44.699
You've saved a lot of
money, plus my money.

1:05:44.733 --> 1:05:45.700
It would be enough.

1:05:46.597 --> 1:05:48.703
I don't know. Besides--

1:05:49.531 --> 1:05:51.085
Besides what?

1:05:51.119 --> 1:05:55.330
Our relationship. I don't
think it's mature enough.

1:05:55.365 --> 1:05:57.608
I mean, a serious
couple should have

1:05:57.643 --> 1:06:00.197
at least one shared
bank account.

1:06:00.232 --> 1:06:03.580
And if we buy a house
without being married

1:06:03.614 --> 1:06:06.479
we won't have the same
legal protections.

1:06:06.514 --> 1:06:08.861
We will have to
buy it as a couple.

1:06:08.895 --> 1:06:12.278
Yeah, so that's what we
are. We're just a couple.

1:06:12.313 --> 1:06:15.212
You know, we sign the
title as tenants in common.

1:06:15.247 --> 1:06:19.044
We just co-own the
house, both of us.

1:06:19.078 --> 1:06:20.631
Come on, it's not complicated.

1:06:20.666 --> 1:06:23.600
We just pay half the mortgage,
half of the down payment.

1:06:23.634 --> 1:06:25.878
We both co-own the house.

1:06:25.912 --> 1:06:26.741
It's simple.

1:06:31.435 --> 1:06:35.163
I don't know. Let
me think about it.

1:06:35.198 --> 1:06:40.099
We'll just buy some food,
and we can talk about it.

1:06:40.134 --> 1:06:42.999
[traffic passing]

1:07:01.086 --> 1:07:02.328
Are you okay?

1:07:04.123 --> 1:07:04.951
I'm okay.

1:07:04.986 --> 1:07:06.574
[Phone voice] False.

1:07:06.608 --> 1:07:07.471
What's that?

1:07:07.506 --> 1:07:09.232
That's Mentira.

1:07:09.266 --> 1:07:12.476
I'm testing it, and it looks
like it's working perfectly.

1:07:14.892 --> 1:07:16.342
What's going on?

1:07:16.377 --> 1:07:18.862
If we're gonna make the
decision of buying a house

1:07:18.896 --> 1:07:22.590
together, we're gonna
make it inside the circle.

1:07:22.624 --> 1:07:23.901
I mean, we can use Mentira.

1:07:26.283 --> 1:07:27.698
We're doing it old school.

1:07:35.499 --> 1:07:36.707
Speak with your heart.

1:07:38.330 --> 1:07:39.745
Okay, okay.

1:07:41.091 --> 1:07:43.507
Do you wanna buy
a house with me?

1:07:43.542 --> 1:07:44.612
Yeah.

1:07:44.646 --> 1:07:45.475
[Phone voice] True.

1:07:55.761 --> 1:07:57.728
Do you think that
buying a house with me

1:07:57.763 --> 1:08:00.110
is a step forward
in our relationship?

1:08:00.145 --> 1:08:01.422
Of course.

1:08:01.456 --> 1:08:02.388
How?

1:08:02.423 --> 1:08:04.149
We are already living together,

1:08:04.183 --> 1:08:07.013
and we're sharing expenses
and responsibilities.

1:08:08.153 --> 1:08:09.947
This one would be a bigger one,

1:08:09.982 --> 1:08:12.191
like more commitment
to the relationship.

1:08:13.123 --> 1:08:16.953
Plus, it'd be our first
investment as a couple.

1:08:18.163 --> 1:08:19.129
That's big.

1:08:20.095 --> 1:08:21.304
Equal parts?

1:08:21.337 --> 1:08:22.649
Yeah.

1:08:22.684 --> 1:08:23.513
Okay.

1:08:25.584 --> 1:08:26.447
It's my turn now.

1:08:36.422 --> 1:08:38.183
[phone ticking]

1:08:40.425 --> 1:08:43.671
What do you want?

1:08:43.705 --> 1:08:46.260
I wanna buy a house, and

1:08:47.468 --> 1:08:49.849
I do wanna buy a house with you.

1:08:49.884 --> 1:08:50.711
[Phone voice] True.

1:08:57.547 --> 1:09:00.514
But I don't wanna
buy it like this.

1:09:00.550 --> 1:09:01.378
[Phone voice] True.

1:09:05.210 --> 1:09:07.833
It sounds more like a
business proposition

1:09:07.867 --> 1:09:11.871
than a couple moving forward
with their relationship.

1:09:13.907 --> 1:09:16.979
Most couples buy a house
because they're married

1:09:17.014 --> 1:09:19.741
or they plan to do so.

1:09:19.776 --> 1:09:23.124
Because they're gonna build
a future in that house.

1:09:24.505 --> 1:09:26.471
But you don't
believe in marriage.

1:09:26.506 --> 1:09:29.958
And I respect that, but
I don't wanna buy a house

1:09:29.993 --> 1:09:33.824
for equity or to
diversify my money.

1:09:35.240 --> 1:09:37.551
If I was to buy
a house with you,

1:09:39.589 --> 1:09:44.387
it would be because we're
gonna fill it with love

1:09:45.559 --> 1:09:48.839
and a family and
a future together.

1:09:53.499 --> 1:09:54.431
I love you.

1:09:56.157 --> 1:09:57.123
I really do.

1:10:00.023 --> 1:10:04.165
Maybe it's, it's like you say.

1:10:08.790 --> 1:10:10.585
Love is not enough.

1:10:10.620 --> 1:10:11.897
[Phone voice] True.

1:10:15.245 --> 1:10:17.316
I don't wanna buy
a house with you.

1:10:21.493 --> 1:10:23.460
At least not right now.

1:10:23.495 --> 1:10:24.323
[Phone voice] True.

1:10:25.393 --> 1:10:26.222
So when?

1:10:29.052 --> 1:10:30.571
When would be the right moment?

1:10:32.434 --> 1:10:34.091
Feels like never.

1:10:34.126 --> 1:10:37.025
[soft piano music]

1:11:00.428 --> 1:11:03.017
[bird calling]

1:11:04.121 --> 1:11:06.916
[soft piano music]

1:11:27.144 --> 1:11:28.525
Where were you?

1:11:30.077 --> 1:11:31.632
I've been calling you all day.

1:11:37.776 --> 1:11:38.777
We need to talk.

1:11:41.124 --> 1:11:41.952
Talk.

1:11:45.541 --> 1:11:47.337
I've been thinking
a lot about us.

1:11:50.375 --> 1:11:51.859
About our relationship.

1:11:57.485 --> 1:12:00.350
Giancarlo, the love
I feel for you,

1:12:03.180 --> 1:12:04.353
I never felt before.

1:12:10.395 --> 1:12:12.327
But I'm just realizing that

1:12:14.639 --> 1:12:17.850
you are never gonna give
me the life I dreamed of.

1:12:20.474 --> 1:12:21.785
I don't understand why.

1:12:24.892 --> 1:12:26.652
We can buy the
house that you want.

1:12:28.205 --> 1:12:31.898
We can fill it with
children, love,

1:12:33.349 --> 1:12:34.142
A cat.

1:12:35.627 --> 1:12:37.249
Everything that you want.

1:12:38.802 --> 1:12:41.909
We can occupy the same
space as a married couple,

1:12:43.013 --> 1:12:46.568
with the same feelings,
the same feelings.

1:12:48.847 --> 1:12:50.780
We just don't have
that contract.

1:12:52.644 --> 1:12:55.267
It's not just the contract.

1:12:56.993 --> 1:12:59.960
It's what the
contract represents.

1:13:01.998 --> 1:13:05.967
It's the wedding, the dress.

1:13:06.002 --> 1:13:08.522
It's saying in front of
everybody that we know

1:13:08.556 --> 1:13:10.213
that we love each other.

1:13:10.246 --> 1:13:13.665
It's saying before God that
we will take care of us

1:13:13.699 --> 1:13:16.875
till death tear us apart.

1:13:16.909 --> 1:13:18.255
But what's the difference?

1:13:18.290 --> 1:13:21.500
I can buy a huge thing
saying I love you.

1:13:21.535 --> 1:13:24.952
I can say it on the radio,
tell God that I love you.

1:13:26.746 --> 1:13:29.957
The commitment I have
for you needs no paper.

1:13:31.855 --> 1:13:35.411
No paper, the commitment
is my love for you.

1:13:39.068 --> 1:13:41.106
And I wanna live by
your side forever.

1:13:42.934 --> 1:13:45.628
Not even death will
break us apart.

1:13:52.219 --> 1:13:53.601
What if we have kids?

1:13:55.050 --> 1:13:56.570
What are we gonna tell them?

1:13:56.603 --> 1:13:58.019
What?

1:13:58.054 --> 1:13:59.227
That we're not married?

1:14:01.609 --> 1:14:04.335
You know how many kids grow
up without a dad or a mom?

1:14:05.682 --> 1:14:08.340
Every family is different.

1:14:08.374 --> 1:14:10.480
You're just stuck with the
ritual that you grew up with,

1:14:10.514 --> 1:14:12.137
and you can't get it
out of your system.

1:14:12.171 --> 1:14:13.241
Stop with the ritual please.

1:14:13.276 --> 1:14:14.588
But it's true, Rocio.

1:14:16.348 --> 1:14:18.454
It's not about that.

1:14:19.351 --> 1:14:21.041
Can't you see?

1:14:22.250 --> 1:14:24.183
It's about us.

